data.text:
Woodrow Wilson Center Press shares in the mission of the Wilson Center by publishing outstanding scholarly and public-policy books for a worldwide readership. Written by the Center’s international network of scholars and its expert staff, our books concentrate on subjects of the Center’s greatest strength, especially energy, security, environmental and social resilience, urban studies, U.S. foreign policy, Cold War history, and area studies.

The Wilson Center, chartered by Congress as the official memorial to President Woodrow Wilson, is the nation’s key nonpartisan policy forum for tackling global issues through independent research and open dialogue to inform actionable ideas for Congress, the administration, and the broader policy community. Visit us at www.wilsoncenter.org.
